---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About Gambitive"
  lede="We explain what tech and startup news actually means, and we let leaders tell the stories they don't tell anywhere else."
>
  <p>
    A gambit is a calculated opening: giving something up now for a better
    position later. Founders make that trade every week. Gambitive exists to
    make sense of those moves — the news, the noise, and the announcements
    coming out of {SITE.niche}.
  </p>
  <p>
    We're not first, and we don't try to be. Plenty of places will tell you a
    funding round happened twenty minutes after the press release lands. We'd
    rather tell you what it means, who it affects, and what the people involved
    learned the hard way.
  </p>
  <h2>What we publish</h2>
  <p>
    <strong><a href="/latest/">Latest</a></strong> — what happened, and why it
    matters, fast. Short, and only when there's a "why it matters" worth your
    time.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong><a href="/deep-dives/">Deep Dives</a></strong> — the analysis
    nobody else is doing. Original reporting and reconstruction, not rewritten
    coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong><a href="/the-hard-part/">The Hard Part</a></strong> — founders and
    operators on the decisions that went wrong, with real numbers. Never paid,
    never PR-approved. <a href="/editorial-policy/">Our editorial policy</a>
    covers how we keep it that way.
  </p>
  <h2>Who it's for</h2>
  <p>
    Founders, operators, investors, and serious professionals in the ecosystem.
    We assume you're smart and short on time, so every piece has to earn its
    length. No filler, no clickbait, no listicles.
  </p>
  <p>
    The best way to read us is the <a href="/newsletter/">weekly newsletter</a>.
    Questions, tips, corrections: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
